# ============================================
# What TO COMMIT (explicitly allowed)
# ============================================
# These are the core IaC files that SHOULD be versioned:
# - manifests-aws/*.yaml (Kubernetes manifests)
# - ansible-aws/*.yml (Ansible playbooks)
# - code/ (Application code and Dockerfiles)
# - *.md (Documentation)
# - scripts/*.sh (Automation scripts)
# - .github/ (CI/CD workflows)
# - cluster-config.yaml (Cluster definitions)
# - Dockerfile* (Container definitions)

# ============================================
# Chapter 4 Principle: "Define Everything as Code"
# ============================================
# This .gitignore ensures we version:
# 1. Infrastructure definitions (manifests, playbooks)
# 2. Application code (Dockerfiles, source code)
# 3. Configuration as code (network policies, HPA, etc)
# 4. Automation scripts (CI/CD, monitoring)
# 5. Documentation (explaining the "how" and "why")
#
# While excluding:
# - Secrets and credentials
# - Build artifacts and temporary files
# - IDE-specific configurations
# - Runtime logs and state files
